      width=3D20></A></TD>
    <TD vAlign=3Dtop width=3D400><FONT face=3D"Arial, Helvetica">On =
Windows NT=20
      systems, it sometimes seems that Microsoft Office products are not =

      recognizing the presence of an ODMA compliant document management =
system=20
      (DMS). This typically occurs when the DMS is installed after =
Office, and=20
      an essential Registry entry is missing. This tells Office to =
handle=20
      switching from Unicode to ANSI for the DMS. If you click on the =
download=20
      icon, you will get a registry update file which can add this entry =
for=20
      you.&nbsp; </FONT></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE>
